title: The Dark Matter of Love (Documentary)
description:
The Dark Matter of Love

URL: thedarkmatteroflove.com

Video: AVC
Audio: AAC
Resolution: 832x468
Frame Rate: 25fps

Documentary in which director Sarah McCarthy explores a year in the lives of Claudio and Cheryl Diaz, former Disney employees from Wisconsin who decided to adopt three Russian children who had previously grown up in care institutions. The film details how Claudio and Cheryl, along with their biological daughter Cami, struggled to form strong familial bonds with the new additions, and turned to developmental psychologist Dr Robert Marvin to help them find a scientifically proven way to teach the youngsters how to love for the first time.
